                            <comment id="12986219" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 25 Jan 2011 04:39:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;First stab at the problem. All existing unit tests pass. Need also a test of intra row scanning with reader change to confirm.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12989530" author="stack" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2011 06:36:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 Seems fine Andrew, especially if all tests passed.  If is a problem, we&apos;ll know how to write a unit test then (I don&apos;t know how you&apos;d easily unit test this now).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12989544" author="ryanobjc" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2011 07:39:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this looks good. if tests demonstrate bug then big +1 on commit&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12989568" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2011 09:12:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I hacked TestWideScanner to generate deep versioned test data and then reach in and update readers:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
@@ -133,11 +139,19 @@ &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; class TestWideScanner &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; HBaseTestCase {
         }
 
         results.clear();
+
+        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// trigger ChangedReadersObservers
&lt;/span&gt;+        Iterator&amp;lt;KeyValueScanner&amp;gt; scanners =
+          ((HRegion.RegionScanner)s).storeHeap.getHeap().iterator();
+        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (scanners.hasNext()) {
+          StoreScanner ss = (StoreScanner)scanners.next();
+          ss.updateReaders();
+        }
       } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (more);
 
       &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; that the scanner returned all values
&lt;/span&gt;       LOG.info(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;inserted &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + inserted + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;, scanned &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + total);
-      assertTrue(total == inserted);
+      assertEquals(total, inserted);
 
       s.close();
     } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;finally&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All seems to work. Do you want that kind of layering violation in the suite though? Will be brittle. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12989680" author="stack" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2011 15:50:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 We do this all over the place to get a test in.  When we rewrite it all, we&apos;ll do it so you don&apos;t have to do such hackery.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12989728" author="ryanobjc" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2011 18:03:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That looks great to me. Other tests have done worse &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12990001" author="apurtell" created="Thu, 3 Feb 2011 07:43:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Passes test on trunk and 0.90 brnach.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
